Preliminary Wrangling¶

This data set includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area. The dataset is gotten from https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2020/October/5f91cf38_201902-fordgobike-tripdata/201902-fordgobike-tripdata.csv¶

The Data Each trip is anonymized and includes:

  • Trip Duration (seconds)
  • Start Time and Date
  • End Time and Date
  • Start Station ID
  • Start Station Name
  • Start Station Latitude
  • Start Station Longitude
  • End Station ID
  • End Station Name
  • End Station Latitude
  • End Station Longitude
  • Bike ID
  • User Type (Subscriber or Customer Subscriber = Member or Customer = Casual)
  • Member Birth Year
  • Member Gender
  • Bike Share for all Trips

  • The time variables in this dataset are all string. They need to be converted to datetime format for the analysis.
  • The time variables can be broken down into time of day, day of the week, or month of the year.
  • The dataset provides membership birth year, so ages can be derived by using the year of the dataset, 2017, to divide by the membership birth year.

The main features of interest in this dataset

My interest is to know where and when most trips are taken in terms of the hour of the day or day of the week and differ between Customers and Subscribers.

Does the average duration of a bike trip depend on whether a user is a Subscriber or Customer?

What bike stations are the most popular destination? And does it differ much dependent upon user_type?

I am also interested in the characteristics of the riders (age, sex, and user_type) and the duration of the trips in these time points and locations.

The features in the dataset expect to support the investigation into the features of interest.

I expect morning and afternoon will have more trips than night due to rush hours. I also assume younger riders will be more than older riders. Also, I expect subscribers to be more than customers. And it's hard to expect female riders to be more than males so that I will check it out in the analysis.

Summary of identified Quality and Tidiness issues¶

Quality issues¶

  • A. starttime and endtime have the wrong datatype string (in stead of datetime)
  • B. start_station_id has wong datatype int64 (in stead of str)
  • C. user_type has wrong datatype string (in stead of categorical)
  • D. There is 17,318 missing values presented in 6 columns in the dataset (start_station_id, start_station_name, end_station_id, end_station_name, member_birth_year and Member_gender).

Tidiness issues¶

non

Observation¶

Most trips are taken on Thursdays, with the peak period being binomial (morning and afternoon), between hours of This suggests that most people especially subscribers take bike rides to work, however, most customers take bike rides within the hours of 8 AM and 6 PM and mostly on weekends which suggests it might be for leisure or tourism.

Average trips take around 10 mins for both subscribers and customers which suggests the distance for the rides is not far.

Market St at 10th St and San Francisco Caltrain Station 2 (Townsend St at 4th St) are the most popular start points with San Francisco Caltrain Station 2 (Townsend St at 4th St) and Market St at 10th St are the most popular destinations. However, there are more customers at San Francisco Ferry Building (Harry Bridges Plaza), Powell St BART Station (Market St at 4th St), and Berry St at 4th St stations than at other stations. There are more customers going to San Francisco Ferry Building (Harry Bridges Plaza), San Francisco Caltrain Station 2 (Townsend St at 4th St) and The Embarcadero at Sansome stations than at other stations. San Francisco Ferry Building (Harry Bridges Plaza) seems to be a very popular place for customers. This suggests it,s a tourist attraction site.

The males also take more bike rides than females even though the females use more duration during the bike rides. The users with age 27 - 37 take the bike rides more. This suggests they mostly take bike rides to work.
